## Data Access

This project does not use a traditional labeled dataset for training. Instead, it uses a pre-trained deep learning model (VGG16) that has already been trained on the ImageNet dataset.

### Model Data Source
- The VGG16 model was pre-trained on the ImageNet dataset
- ImageNet contains over 14 million labeled images across 1000+ categories
- The dataset includes everyday objects such as animals, vehicles, and household items

### User Input Data
- Images are provided by the user at runtime
- Supported formats: JPG, PNG, JPEG
- Images are uploaded through a Jupyter Notebook file upload widget

### Preprocessing Requirements
Before being passed into the model, each image is:
- Resized to 224x224 pixels
- Converted into a numerical array
- Normalized using VGG16 preprocessing standards

### Note
No external dataset download is required to run this project. All required data is either:
- Built into the pre-trained model (ImageNet weights)
- Provided by the user during execution
